column5: Just down at the lock in Lindsay and there are walleye in for the start of the spawn if anyone wants to check it out. They're on the south side.
Terry grabs fashlight, headlamp.. spear.. black clothing.  Great to know there gettin it on Jimmer.. not great to point out where some days though.
I will be down that way on Tuesday...will take a look...  BTW...The Boss (TJ) sez they are called pickerel...
no no no... everything but the spear oh  and I bring the underwater camera and get some real fish porn.......
Pickerel look like small pike...you must mean Yellow Pike.
What you are talking about are Chain Pickerel Bob.pickerel is Pickerel,Dore, Yellow Pickerel,.. How come i cant type pickerel? See, every time i type pickerel, it says pickerel

I know what a chain pickerel is...Canadian's call them grass pike....we catch them in Oneida Lake all the time while fishing for Yellow Pike (pickerel)....   Yellow Pike is a Buffalo nickname for pickerel because Lake Erie once had Blue Pike...
thank you for the pickerel filter   someone has a good sense of homour
You got that all correct expect "Blue Pike" WERE a cousin of the Yellow Pike...but a now extinct species.
